function RENDER {
    print("<!doctype html><html lang='en'><head><meta name='viewport' content='width=device-width,initial-scale=1'><title>Capy Implementation Status</title><link rel='stylesheet' href='style.css'></head><body><div class='shell'><header class='top'><strong><a href='index.capy'>Capy Reference</a></strong><span>Implementation status</span></header><div class='layout'><nav aria-label='Reference chapters'><a href='index.capy'>Overview</a><a href='syntax.capy'>Syntax</a><a href='types.capy'>Types & overloads</a><a href='ownership.capy'>ARC ownership</a><a href='interop.capy'>Bearer interop</a><a class='active' aria-current='page' href='status.capy'>Implementation status</a></nav><main><h1>Implementation status</h1><p>This page deliberately separates shipped behavior from reserved or planned language work.</p><h2>Implemented</h2><ul><li>Direct Wasm compilation and Bearer artifact publication.</li><li>Expression-slot function declarations and lexical scopes.</li><li><code>s32</code>, <code>bool</code>, strings, arrays, structs, tuples, and copied <code>dval</code>.</li><li>Arithmetic, comparisons, assignment, if, while, ranges, array iteration, break, and continue.</li><li>ARC-managed markup values with escaped UCE-style interpolation, trusted composition, scalar formatting, and batched output.</li><li>Exact overloads, compile-time <code>any</code>, <code>x::type</code>, ambiguity rejection, and specialization caching.</li><li>Managed tuple returns and static tuple indexing.</li><li>Scalar <code>as</code> casts, public fixed-signature function types, and ARC-managed capturing lambdas.</li><li>Workspace-local ARC with nested drop glue and trap containment.</li><li>CLI, RENDER, COMPONENT, named handlers, WS, ONCE, INIT, and SERVE_HTTP export surfaces.</li><li>Capy-to-C++ and C++-to-Capy Bearer dispatch.</li><li>Structured dval maps/lists, strict indexing and extraction, explicit missing checks, ordered iteration, and Capy custom exports.</li><li>Expression-level source maps for bounds, DValue, allocation, explicit trap, and function-entry locations.</li></ul><h2>Planned</h2><ul><li>Complete inference and broader malformed-input recovery.</li><li>Variadic declaration syntax and conversion-ranked overload candidates.</li><li>Weak references for deliberate cycles.</li><li>Struct reflection iteration and metadata access.</li></ul><h2>Deliberately deferred</h2><p><code>#compile</code> and <code>#callsite</code> are reserved beyond phase 3 and produce targeted parser diagnostics. <code>emit</code> is also reserved but does not yet have dedicated syntax or diagnostics. No compile-time programs execute.</p><div class='note'>The language is under active development. This reference tracks the current Capy implementation on Bearer ABI c18/w11.</div></main></div></div></body></html>")
}
